4. Business Model (Simple & Realistic)
Phase 1 ‚Äì Manual (No Tech Cost)

Revenue Model: Fixed Service Fee

Example:

Client order: 10,000 ETB

WarkaHub fee: 500‚Äì1,000 ETB flat

Vendor receives full price (no % confusion)

üëâ This avoids commission fights.

Phase 2 ‚Äì Semi-Automated

Platform suggests vendors

WarkaHub charges:

Fixed fee OR

Subscription from vendors (monthly)

Phase 3 ‚Äì Full Platform

Small % commission (5‚Äì10%)

Escrow-style payments

Premium vendor visibility

5. MVP Scope (What to Build First)
MVP Goal:

Validate demand, earn first money, learn behavior

MVP = Manual + WhatsApp + Google Sheets
Client Flow (Manual)

Client messages WarkaHub (Telegram / WhatsApp)

WarkaHub collects:

Service type

Date

Location

Budget

WarkaHub matches vendor manually

Vendor confirms

Client confirms

Service delivered

WarkaHub collects fee

Vendor Flow (Manual)

Vendor registers via Google Form

WarkaHub verifies manually

Vendor added to vendor list

Receives jobs via Telegram/Call

Delivers service

Gets paid directly by client

6. Manual Matching Process (Step-by-Step)

Client submits request

Filter vendors by:

Location

Availability

Price range

Send request to top 2‚Äì3 vendors

First confirmation wins

Lock vendor

Notify client

Track delivery

Collect WarkaHub fee

7. Why This Works (Ride Logic)
Ride App	WarkaHub
Rider	Client
Driver	Vendor
Ride request	Service request
Fare	Service price
App fee	Hub fee

You‚Äôre not inventing behavior ‚Äî you‚Äôre copying proven logic.

